description:
Watch as the story of Joseph from Genesis chapter 50 comes to life in iBIBLEthe worlds first visual and interactive Bible. Featured in the 42nd episode of iBIBLE are the stories of Jacobs (Israels) burial, Josephs reassurance to his brothers, and Josephs death. Before his death, Joseph makes the sons of Israel promise to carry his bones out of Egypt. Study the Bible and enjoy the narrative presentation of Gods Word with iBIBLE.

A production of RevelationMedia, iBIBLE brings Gods Word to life in a format that people all over the world can engage with. Through dramatic audio and vibrant animation, people of all ages, all backgrounds, and with all abilities can learn the Biblical Narrativethe one cohesive story of Scripture. iBIBLE will be available for free to translate into any of the worlds 7,000+ languages. Join the movement today and help bring the true story of Gods Word to the nations for free!

Visit www.iBIBLE.app to see all completed episodes of iBIBLEa visual Bible for a visual and connected world! 

Director: Steve Cleary
